#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:8
msgid "Generic Loader"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:10
msgid ""
"The 'loader' device allows the user to load multiple images or values into "
"QEMU at startup."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:14
msgid "Loading Data into Memory Values"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:15
msgid ""
"The loader device allows memory values to be set from the command line. This "
"can be done by following the syntax below::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:18
msgid ""
"-device loader,addr=<addr>,data=<data>,data-len=<data-len> \\\n"
"                [,data-be=<data-be>][,cpu-num=<cpu-num>]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:21 ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:57
#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:83
msgid "``<addr>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:22
msgid "The address to store the data in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:24 ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:60
#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:87
msgid ""
"Note that as usual with QEMU numeric option values, the default is to treat "
"the argument as decimal.  To specify a value in hex, prefix it with '0x'."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:28
msgid "``<data>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:29
msgid ""
"The value to be written to the address. The maximum size of the data is 8 "
"bytes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:32
msgid "``<data-len>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:33
msgid ""
"The length of the data in bytes. This argument must be included if the data "
"argument is."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:36
msgid "``<data-be>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:37
msgid ""
"Set to true if the data to be stored on the guest should be written as big "
"endian data. The default is to write little endian data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:40 ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:64
#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:91
msgid "``<cpu-num>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:41
msgid ""
"The number of the CPU's address space where the data should be loaded. If "
"not specified the address space of the first CPU is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:45
msgid "An example of loading value 0x8000000e to address 0xfd1a0104 is::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:47
msgid "-device loader,addr=0xfd1a0104,data=0x8000000e,data-len=4"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:50
msgid "Setting a CPU's Program Counter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:52
msgid ""
"The loader device allows the CPU's PC to be set from the command line. This "
"can be done by following the syntax below::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:55
msgid "-device loader,addr=<addr>,cpu-num=<cpu-num>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:58
msgid "The value to use as the CPU's PC."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:65
msgid "The number of the CPU whose PC should be set to the specified value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:67
msgid "An example of setting CPU 0's PC to 0x8000 is::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:69
msgid "-device loader,addr=0x8000,cpu-num=0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:72
msgid "Loading Files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:74
msgid ""
"The loader device also allows files to be loaded into memory. It can load "
"ELF, U-Boot, and Intel HEX executable formats as well as raw images.  The "
"syntax is shown below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:78
msgid ""
"-device loader,file=<file>[,addr=<addr>][,cpu-num=<cpu-num>][,force-"
"raw=<raw>]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:80
msgid "``<file>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:81
msgid "A file to be loaded into memory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:84
msgid ""
"The memory address where the file should be loaded. This is required for raw "
"images and ignored for non-raw files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:92
msgid ""
"This specifies the CPU that should be used. This is an optional argument "
"with two effects:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:95
msgid "this CPU's address space is used to load the data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:96
msgid ""
"this CPU's PC will be set to the address where the raw file is loaded or the "
"entry point specified in the executable format header"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:99
msgid ""
"If this option is not specified, then the data will be loaded via the "
"address space of the first CPU, and no CPU will have its PC set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:102
msgid ""
"Note that there is currently no way to specify the address space to load the "
"data without also causing that CPU's PC to be set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:105
msgid ""
"Since it sets the starting PC, this option should only be used for the boot "
"image."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:108
msgid "``<force-raw>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:109
msgid ""
"Setting 'force-raw=on' forces the file to be treated as a raw image. This "
"can be used to load supported executable formats as if they were raw."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:114
msgid "An example of loading an ELF file which CPU0 will boot is shown below::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/generic-loader.rst:116
msgid "-device loader,file=./images/boot.elf,cpu-num=0"
msgstr ""
